The paper deals with the problem of computing the greedy spanner, which is a geometric graph problem. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses optimizations to the running time, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also mentions the maximal degree of the spanner, which is a graph-theoretic property, indicating that it may belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implementation of the algorithm, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
